text: Jean François de Noailles, Marquis of Noailles 28 August 1658 - 23 June 1692) was a French nobleman and was known by his title of "Marquis of Noailles" (marquis de Noailles) He was a member of the influential House of Noailles. He was also a "Maréchal de camp" ==Children== Noailles married Marguerite Thérèse Rouillé in 1687 and had two daughters. #Louise Antoinette de Noailles (25 February 1688 - 21 August 1690) died in infancy. #Anne Catherine de Noailles (28 September 1694 - 7 November 1716) married Armand de Vignerot du Plessis, Duke of Richelieu but had no children.
